Functional Requirements:

-Product Display
The webpage should display a list of products dynamically.
Each product should include a name, image, price, and category.

-Search Functionality
Users should be able to search for products by name using the search bar.

-Filters
Users should filter products by category (e.g., Electronics, Clothing, Home).
Users should filter products by price using a range slider.

-Dynamic Updates
The product list should update dynamically based on search and filter inputs without refreshing the page.

-Responsive Design
The webpage should adapt to different screen sizes, ensuring usability on both desktop and mobile devices.
Clear Reset
Users can clear or reset filters to view the full product list again.

-Interactive Buttons
An "Apply Filters" button should update the product list based on selected filters.


Non-Functional Requirements:

-Performance
The webpage should load in under 2 seconds on a standard broadband connection.
Dynamic updates (filtering and search) should occur within 200ms.

-Accessibility.
The webpage should follow accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1).
Elements should be navigable via keyboard and screen readers.

-Maintainability
Code should follow best practices for readability and modularity.
CSS is stored in an external file to enable easy updates.
JavaScript is separated into a standalone file for improved maintainability.

-Scalability
The solution should handle up to 1000 products without significant performance degradation.
Cross-Browser Compatibility
The webpage should work seamlessly across major browsers like Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge.

-Security
Prevent XSS attacks by sanitizing user inputs in JavaScript.

-Usability
Intuitive and user-friendly interface with clear labels and instructions for search and filtering.

-Error Handling
Inform the user if no products match their search or filter criteria (e.g., display "No products found").